Wednesday, December 4, 1991

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

91-1634. State v. Burney.

Cuyahoga County, No. 58611. This cause is pending before the court on the filing of a motion for leave to appeal from the Court of Appeals for Cuyahoga County and as a claimed appeal as of right from said court.

On October 16, 1991, this court granted appellant’s motion to strike his duplicative memorandum in support of jurisdiction. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that this cause be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, effective December 2, 1991.
